x4freetext: LAMPF A-6 proton target station.
A beam of large diameter, about 50 mm, compared to  the
size of the He accumulation samples so that any spatial
variation of proton fluence within the samples would be
insignificant.
The 4He and 3He contents of the test
materials were determined at Rockwell International
(USA) by mass spectrometry following vaporization of
the specimen under vacuum in a resistance heated
graphite crucible.
Metals of Fe, Cu, Mo and W, as well as, additional
metals of general interest: Al, Au and Ni were used.
The size of the helium accumulation samples (3 mm
diameter by 0.1 mm thickness).
The samples that were analyzed for helium content, were
sandwiched between thick samples of the same material
to eliminate any surface effects due to recoil escape
of alpha particles and He-3 atoms.
The Rutherford version of the high energy
nucleon-meson transport code (HETC).
Summary of medium energy protons irradiations damage
parameters.
The  aluminum dosimeter foils were placed in contact
with the test materials so that the proton fluences
would be the same.

x4freetext: For beam fluence measurements.
For 3-He and 4-He contents.
Any information is absent.
1. Any information for experimental accuracy is absent.
2. The production of helium-3 due to radioactive decay
of tritium is not discussed. This production is
possible and tritium production influence depends from
time interval from proton irradiation and helium
content measurement.
